- Mod.MPP]


[Our comment of 10 Mar 2007, to the reported case of leishmaniasis in
Xinjiang province, stated that cases were only seen in the hilly and
newly reclaimed desert areas in northwestern China (Zhi-Biao X:
Present situation of visceral leishmaniasis in China. Parasitol Today
1989;5: 224-8). A review of leishmaniasis in China concluded that
apart from sporadic cases in Xinjiang and western Inner Mongolia
(Guan LR: Current status of Kala Azar and vector control in China.
Bull World Health Organ 1991;69: 595-601). If this case was infected
in Eastern China (Fujian) it seems that leishmaniasis is more
widespread in the country than previously thought.

A map showing the location of Fujian province is available at
<http://encarta.msn.com/map_701510630/Fujian.html>.- Mod.EP]

[To see China with provinces, maps can be found at:
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/middle_east_and_asia/china_pol01.jpg>
- Mod.MPP]
